Date: Tue 2 Aug 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Itar-Tass News agency, 2 Aug 2005 [edited]
<http://www.tass.ru/eng/level2.html?NewsID=2281149&PageNum=0>

65 000 domestic birds to be destroyed in Novosibirsk region over flu
-----------------------------------------------
About 65 000 domestic birds will be destroyed in 13 settlements of
Russia's Novosibirsk region, where quarantine was introduced over
bird flu, the deputy governor of the region told a press conference
on Tuesday [2 Aug 2005].
Although the number of fowl killed by bird flu has declined over the
past few days, a decision was reached to destroy all household
poultry and pay compensation to the population, Viktor Gergert said.
Almost 9 million rubles [USD 315 000] have been earmarked for that
from the regional budget.
So far, no cases of humans being infected with bird flu have been
registered in the Novosibirsk region, sources from the regional
headquarters set up to tackle the problem have said.
