Bird flu rages on the border of Kazakhstan and Russia
-----------------------------------------------
The Berdyuzhskii district in Tyumen oblast, bordering on Kazakhstan,
is under quarantine due to a "flu bird" outbreak, our correspondent
reports.
Official authorities are not commenting. According to unofficial
data, the veterinary administration of the Tyumen oblast government
has begun large scale inspection of all poultry plants.
[Byline: Kalil Kabdulvakhitov]
